text: Amelie Solja (born 29 September 1990) is an Austrian table tennis player, born in Kandel, Germany. She competed in women's team at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London. Her sister Petrissa Solja was a silver medalist at the 2016 Olympic Games for Germany. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Rhineland-Palatinate Category:Austrian female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Austria Category:Table tennis players at the 2012 Summer Olympics Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Austria Category:People from Germersheim (district)
